# Standard: Markdown Text Syntax (SF-SYNTAX-MARKDOWN-TEXT)

## 1. Standard Statement

This standard **MANDATES** the comprehensive Markdown syntax for all text-focused elements: headings, emphasis, links, and blockquotes. This consolidated standard ensures universal consistency for text presentation and navigation across the Knowledge Base.

## 2. Heading Syntax

### Rule 2.1: ATX Style Headings
Headings **MUST** be created exclusively using ATX style with hash symbols (`#`). The number of hash symbols **MUST** correspond to the heading level.
*   **Mandatory Syntax:**
    ```markdown
    # H1 Heading
    ## H2 Heading  
    ### H3 Heading
    #### H4 Heading
    ##### H5 Heading
    ###### H6 Heading
    ```
*   **Prohibited:** Setext style headings (using `=` or `-` below text)

### Rule 2.2: Single Space After Hash Symbols
There **MUST** be a single space character immediately following the hash symbol(s) and preceding the heading text.
*   **Correct:** `# My Heading`
*   **Prohibited:** `#My Heading`, ` # My Heading`

### Rule 2.3: Blank Lines Around Headings
A single blank line **MUST** precede and follow every heading.
*   **Exceptions:**
    *   H1 heading at document beginning (after YAML frontmatter) **MUST NOT** have a blank line before it
    *   Heading at document end **MUST NOT** have a blank line after it

### Rule 2.4: Single H1 Heading for Document Title
Each document **MUST** contain **exactly one** H1 heading as the first content element after YAML frontmatter.

### Rule 2.5: Strict Hierarchical Heading Progression
Heading levels **MUST** be used in strict hierarchical order without skipping levels.
*   **Correct:** H1 → H2 → H3 → H3 → H2 → H3 → H4
*   **Prohibited:** H1 → H3 (skips H2), H2 → H4 (skips H3)

## 3. Emphasis Syntax

### Rule 3.1: Italic Emphasis
Italic emphasis **MUST** be created exclusively using single asterisks (`*`).
*   **Mandatory Syntax:** `*italic text*`
*   **Prohibited:** Single underscores (`_italic text_`)

### Rule 3.2: Bold Emphasis
Bold emphasis **MUST** be created exclusively using double asterisks (`**`).
*   **Mandatory Syntax:** `**bold text**`
*   **Prohibited:** Double underscores (`__bold text__`)

### Rule 3.3: Combined Bold and Italic Emphasis
Combined bold and italic emphasis **MUST** be created using triple asterisks (`***`).
*   **Mandatory Syntax:** `***bold and italic text***`
*   **Prohibited:** Any combination of underscores and asterisks

## 4. Link Syntax

### Rule 4.1: External Links
External links **MUST** use standard Markdown inline link format.
*   **Mandatory Syntax:** `[Link Display Text](URL)`
*   **Example:** `[Official W3C Website](https://www.w3.org/)`

### Rule 4.2: Internal Links to Standard Documents
Internal links to documents with `standard_id` **MUST** use the `[[STANDARD_ID]]` syntax.
*   **Mandatory Syntax:** `[[STANDARD_ID]]` or `[[STANDARD_ID|Display Text]]`
*   **Examples:**
    ```markdown
    See [[AS-STRUCTURE-KB-ROOT]]
    Refer to [[SF-SYNTAX-EMPHASIS|Text Emphasis Standard]]
    ```

### Rule 4.3: Section Links
To link to specific headings within documents, append the heading text with `#`.
*   **Mandatory Syntax:** `[[STANDARD_ID#Heading Text]]` or `[[STANDARD_ID#Heading Text|Display Text]]`
*   **Example:** `[[AS-STRUCTURE-KB-ROOT#Master Table of Contents]]`

### Rule 4.4: Internal Links to Non-Standard Documents
Links to documents without `standard_id` **MUST** use relative paths from repository root.
*   **Mandatory Syntax:** `[Link Text](./path/from/repo/root/to/document.md)`
*   **Example:** `[Project Guidelines](./active-project/project-guidelines/project-reminders.md)`

### Rule 4.5: Autolinks
Raw URLs and email addresses **MUST** be enclosed in angle brackets for automatic linking.
*   **Syntax:** `<https://www.example.com>` or `<contact@example.com>`

### Rule 4.6: Prohibited Link Formats
*   **Reference-style links** are **PROHIBITED**
*   **Direct file paths to standard documents** are **PROHIBITED** (use `[[STANDARD_ID]]` instead)

### Rule 4.7: Descriptive Link Text
Link display text **MUST** clearly indicate the content or purpose of the destination. Generic text like "click here" is **PROHIBITED**.

## 5. Blockquote Syntax

### Rule 5.1: Blockquote Marker
All blockquote lines **MUST** be prefixed with `> ` (greater-than symbol followed by single space).
*   **Example:**
    ```markdown
    > This is a blockquote.
    > It can span multiple lines.
    ```

### Rule 5.2: Nested Blockquotes
Nested blockquotes **MUST** use additional `>` symbols for each nesting level.
*   **Example:**
    ```markdown
    > First level quote.
    >
    > > Second level nested quote.
    > > Continues on multiple lines.
    >
    > Back to first level.
    ```

### Rule 5.3: Blank Lines Around Blockquotes
Single blank lines **MUST** precede and follow every blockquote element.

## 6. Scope of Application

This standard applies to **ALL** Markdown documents within the Knowledge Base repository. Adherence is **MANDATORY** for all content creators, automated systems, and tooling.

